title: Fleet of Man-o-War in Battle
medium: Brush and gray wash, graphite on cream paperboard tipped into binding with fabric
description: Horizontal sheet bound vertically in album.  Depicted are warships on the ocean, possibly related to 1943-51-96 and 1943-51-94.  The ships are entirely shrouded by smoke or fog.  The scene has a chaotic feel, and it is not possible to discern the ships beyond those in the foreground.
name: Album page
